          "guid": "mryh3661cke9czx8",
          "message": {
            "text": "Every caret / selection assertion in this file reduces to one model:\n`position = TEXT_X0 + n * ADV`, where **TEXT_X0 (52) is fixed by the layout**\n(36px line-number column + 12px padding + 4px window inset) and **only the\nper-character advance varies with the face**. The original assertions baked in\nMenlo's advance (7.52px at 12.5px) as pixel literals, so the Linux container —\nwhich has no Menlo and substitutes a narrower mono — missed every window low.\n\nCross-check that the model is right, not just convenient: the old literals divide\nback to whole character columns — (172.4−52)/7.52 = 16, (247.7−52)/7.52 = 26,\n(194.9−52)/7.52 = 19 — which is why `col(16)`, `col(26)`, `col(19)` reproduce\nthem exactly. `ADV` is measured from the example page itself in `setup()`, so the\nassertions now say what they mean (\"parks on the captured glyph edge\") and hold\non any host regardless of which mono the platform resolves.\n\nNOT pinned to a bundled face (the ticket's other suggestion): the fixture subset\nfont renders on macOS Chrome but not in the Linux container (measured 7.5 vs\n8.0 px/char, and it broke the overlay-vs-page bbox parity by 67px on Linux only)\n— so pinning was net-harmful here, and the measured advance makes it unnecessary.\n",
            "markdown": "Every caret / selection assertion in this file reduces to one model:\n`position = TEXT_X0 + n * ADV`, where **TEXT_X0 (52) is fixed by the layout**\n(36px line-number column + 12px padding + 4px window inset) and **only the\nper-character advance varies with the face**. The original assertions baked in\nMenlo's advance (7.52px at 12.5px) as pixel literals, so the Linux container —\nwhich has no Menlo and substitutes a narrower mono — missed every window low.\n\nCross-check that the model is right, not just convenient: the old literals divide\nback to whole character columns — (172.4−52)/7.52 = 16, (247.7−52)/7.52 = 26,\n(194.9−52)/7.52 = 19 — which is why `col(16)`, `col(26)`, `col(19)` reproduce\nthem exactly. `ADV` is measured from the example page itself in `setup()`, so the\nassertions now say what they mean (\"parks on the captured glyph edge\") and hold\non any host regardless of which mono the platform resolves.\n\nNOT pinned to a bundled face (the ticket's other suggestion): the fixture subset\nfont renders on macOS Chrome but not in the Linux container (measured 7.5 vs\n8.0 px/char, and it broke the overlay-vs-page bbox parity by 67px on Linux only)\n— so pinning was net-harmful here, and the measured advance makes it unnecessary.\n"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "tests/editor-session.e2e.test.ts"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 105,
                  "endLine": 107,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "/** Left edge of character column `n` in the code area, in device px. */\nconst ADV = env?.advance ?? NaN;\nconst col = (n: number): number => TEXT_X0 + n * ADV;"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
